BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 266.89 Td (are local to the current rank. A prefix-sum and scatter phase converts this token-major routing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 253.89 Td (result into an expert-major queue. Each queue entry stores the original token identifier and the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 240.89 Td (associated routing weight. The GEMM stages therefore process contiguous row ranges for each local) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 227.89 Td (expert rather than branching over token-major top-k slots.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 210.89 Td (After compaction, the first compute stage evaluates W13 and applies SwiGLU within the same Triton) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 197.89 Td (program. It loads FP8 hidden blocks and FP8 expert weights, multiplies both operands by their) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 184.89 Td (128-element block scales, casts the dequantized operands to BF16 for tl.dot, accumulates in FP32,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 171.89 Td (and stores the intermediate activation as BF16. The second compute stage evaluates W2 on the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 158.89 Td (intermediate activation, multiplies by the stored routing weight, and scatters the result to the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 145.89 Td (original output row. For tokens with a single local expert contribution, the kernel performs a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 132.89 Td (direct store; for tokens with multiple local contributions, it uses relaxed atomic addition. This) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 119.89 Td (distinction avoids BF16 atomics in the common single-local-contribution case.) Tj ET
