BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 643.89 Td (experts. Small deterministic tie-breakers are added before selection to make equality cases stable.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 630.89 Td (During top-k extraction, the kernel writes the selected global expert id, stores the unbiased) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 617.89 Td (sigmoid value for later normalization, increments the local expert count when the expert belongs to) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 604.89 Td (this rank, and records the number of local hits for the token. The same kernel initializes the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 591.89 Td (output row to zero so that the later scatter phase can accumulate without requiring a separate) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 578.89 Td (output fill kernel.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 561.89 Td (For the compact regime, a 32-element prefix-sum kernel computes the starting offset of each local) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 548.89 Td (expert in the expert-major queue, and a scatter kernel uses per-expert atomic cursors to write) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 535.89 Td (\(token_id, routing_weight\) pairs into their contiguous ranges. Since there are only 32 local) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 522.89 Td (experts, the prefix sum is deliberately serial; its cost is small compared with the GEMM work, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 509.89 Td (the resulting layout substantially simplifies downstream kernels.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 492.89 Td (For the small-batch regime, prefix-sum and scatter are fused. Each program owns one local expert,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 479.89 Td (computes its offset from the 32 counts, scans the T * 8 routing slots, and uses tl.cumsum to compact) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 466.89 Td (hits for that expert. This removes both the host count transfer and the cursor-zeroing allocation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 453.89 Td (observed in the intermediate profile for tiny workloads.) Tj ET
