BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 409.89 Td (GEMM1 uses fixed tile parameters BLOCK_M = 128, BLOCK_N = 128, and BLOCK_K = 128, with eight warps) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 396.89 Td (and three pipeline stages. The hidden dimension is therefore traversed in 56 K-tiles. The kernel) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 383.89 Td (computes the gate and up projections in a single pass over the input row block: for each K-tile it) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 370.89 Td (loads one hidden block and two W13 blocks, applies the hidden scale and the corresponding gate/up) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 357.89 Td (weight scales, and accumulates two FP32 matrices. This reuses the hidden-state load and avoids) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 344.89 Td (writing the 4096-dimensional W13 result to memory. The final operation is gate * silu\(up\), stored as) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 331.89 Td (a 2048-dimensional BF16 intermediate.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 314.89 Td (GEMM2 uses BLOCK_N = 128 over the 7168 output dimension and BLOCK_K = 64 over the 2048 intermediate) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 301.89 Td (dimension. BLOCK_M is selected from two manual configurations: 32 rows for small expert queues and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 288.89 Td (64 rows when the maximum expert count is at least 64. The larger M tile improves arithmetic density) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 275.89 Td (for large queues, while the smaller tile reduces wasted work and register pressure for sparse) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 262.89 Td (queues. The scale index along the output dimension is computed per column, which keeps the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 249.89 Td (implementation correct even when an N-tile crosses a 128-column scale-block boundary.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 232.89 Td (The design intentionally specializes to the fixed geometry of the MoE track. Constants such as the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 219.89 Td (number of experts, hidden size, intermediate size, top-k, and block size are compile-time constants) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 206.89 Td (in the Triton kernels. This permits aggressive constant propagation and avoids run-time dispatch) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 193.89 Td (overhead. The solution uses Triton tl.dot rather than handwritten CUDA and does not explicitly) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 180.89 Td (invoke Blackwell-specific UMMA or TMA primitives. This choice prioritizes correctness, portability,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.60 Tf 48.00 167.89 Td (and predictable code generation in the evaluation environment for compute capability 10.0.) Tj ET
